<paragraph id="B3003682FFE2F874FF1AF894BF3AE2B5" blockId="104.[151,1436,1884,2022]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE2F874FF1AF894BA38E222" bold="true" box="[151,283,1884,1905]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">FIGURE 52.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE2F874FEAFF894B945E222" authority="Hodgson &amp; Peronti" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Peronti" authorityYear="2012" box="[290,614,1884,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="danieleae" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE2F874FEAFF894BABEE222" box="[290,413,1884,1905]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">C. danieleae</emphasis>
Hodgson &amp; Peronti
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9AF857EBFFE2F874FDFFF894B9F7E222" box="[626,724,1884,1905]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Holotype. For explanation of labels, see p. 9. Notes: (i) dorsal loculate microducts of rusci-type; (ii) dorsal clear area with many dorsal setae; (iii) dorsal setae longer than width of basal socket; (iv) stigmatic setae extending only a very short distance out of cleft along margin; (v) stigmatic setae in each cleft all subequal in size; (vi) multilocular disc-pores only present posteriorly on abdomen; (vii) ventral tubular ducts present anteriorly and (extremely few) posteriorly; (viii) tibio-tarsal articulatory sclerosis present, and (ix) claw digitules both broad.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="B3003682FFE3F875FF4AFF50B994E5FC" blockId="105.[151,1437,151,2012]" box="[199,695,151,176]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FF4AFF50BBDCE5E3" bold="true" box="[199,255,152,176]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Note</emphasis>
