</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FED1FA38B975E35B" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Peronti" authorityYear="2012" box="[348,598,1520,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="danieleae">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FED1FA38B975E35B" box="[348,598,1520,1544]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Ceroplastes danieleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FCABFA38B85FE354" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Peronti" authorityYear="2012" box="[806,892,1520,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mori">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FCABFA38B85FE354" box="[806,892,1520,1544]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">C. mori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(described as new below in the 
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FB61FA38BEB0E35B" box="[1260,1427,1520,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="theobromae">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FB61FA38BEB0E35B" box="[1260,1427,1520,1544]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">C. theobromae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- group) – and, indeed, was initially identified as such. However, importantly, it has a large group of tubular ducts in the cephalic region, absent on 
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FE7EF9F0B969E31C" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Peronti" authorityYear="2012" box="[499,586,1592,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mori">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FE7EF9F0B969E31C" box="[499,586,1592,1616]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">C. mori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Green clearly recognised this as different when he gave this material the manuscript name 
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FEECF994BAF0E327" box="[353,467,1628,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solidus">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FEECF994BAF0E327" box="[353,467,1628,1652]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">C. solidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but unfortunately he left no notes as to what this species looked like in life. On the other hand, his suggested specific name can surely only refer to the wax which is therefore likely to be firm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B3003682FFE3F875FF4AF96CBA02E21F" blockId="105.[151,1437,151,2012]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
The placement of this species in the 
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FDEDF96CB99AE3EF" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[608,697,1700,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rusci">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FDEDF96CB99AE3EF" box="[608,697,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">C. rusci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group rather than in the 
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FC5CF96CBF54E3EF" box="[977,1143,1700,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="theobromae">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FC5CF96CBF54E3EF" box="[977,1143,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">C. theobromae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group is open to question but none of the other species in the 
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FDABF900B9E8E3B3" box="[550,715,1736,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="theobromae">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FDABF900B9E8E3B3" box="[550,715,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">C. theobromae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group have tubular ducts in the cephalic region. In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FA0FF900BA27E257" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Peronti" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="danieleae">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FA0FF900BA27E257" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">C. danieleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has distinct tibio-tarsal articulatory scleroses and many specimens also had a few (up to 3) stigmatic setae extending out of each cleft along the margin. All of these characters suggest a closer relationship to the 
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FA0FF8D8BBECE21F" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rusci">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FA0FF8D8BBECE21F" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">C. rusci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B3003682FFE3F875FF4AF890B928E2C7" blockId="105.[151,1437,151,2012]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
At the present time, 
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FE39F890B966E223" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Peronti" authorityYear="2012" box="[436,581,1880,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="danieleae">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FE39F890B966E223" box="[436,581,1880,1904]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">C. danieleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the original collection in 
<collectingCountry id="CBA87612FFE3F875FBD3F890BBC1E2C7" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Democratic Republic of the Congo</collectingCountry>
on 
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FE81F8B5BA5FE2C0" box="[268,380,1916,1940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Morus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FE81F8B5BA76E2C7" box="[268,341,1917,1940]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Morus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FE07F8B4BADCE2C7" box="[394,511,1916,1940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Moraceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B3003682FFE3F876FF4AF868B819E5A4" blockId="105.[151,1437,151,2012]" lastBlockId="106.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="106" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FF4AF868BABBE2EB" box="[199,408,1951,1976]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" reason="1">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FF4AF868BAB2E2EB" bold="true" box="[199,401,1951,1976]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Name derivation</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This species of 
<taxonomicName id="74BF4D01FFE3F875FDECF868B9C5E2EB" box="[609,742,1952,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="81CBEA90FFE3F875FDECF868B9C5E2EB" box="[609,742,1952,1976]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Ceroplastes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named to honour Dr. Danièle Matile-Ferrero, Laboratoire d’Entomologie, Muséum national d’Histoire naturelle, Paris, who collected some of the material studied for this revision, particularly from areas that have been rarely visited by coccidologists. She also very kindly allowed us to borrow a large number of specimens from the MNHN collection, particularly from countries associated with 
<collectingCountry id="CBA87612FFE0F876FF1AFF28BBC5E5A4" box="[151,230,224,247]" name="France" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">France</collectingCountry>
, thus making the geographical coverage much wider.
</paragraph>
